Patch 0081 — addresses the user's institutional-quality review:
"detect who benefits FROM the bottleneck, not just identify the
bottleneck. Without this category, ARM/AMD/AKAM never appear."

ARCHITECTURE
   constraint (SystemNode)
     → architectural adaptation (causal pattern)
       → beneficiary tickers (accumulated dynamically)

8 ARCHITECTURAL ADAPTATIONS
1. POWER_EFFICIENCY     — perf/watt wins under grid+cooling constraint
                          (ARM, QCOM, AMPC, AAPL, AMD)
2. ALT_ACCELERATOR      — hyperscalers route around NVIDIA/HBM/CoWoS
                          (AMD, AVGO, MRVL, AMZN, GOOG, META)
3. EDGE_INFERENCE       — inference shifts to CDN/edge (centralized too costly)
                          (AKAM, NET, FSLY, EQIX, DLR)
4. BEHIND_THE_METER     — skip the grid via on-site power
                          (BLDP, BE, PLUG, SMR, OKLO, CEG, VST)
5. SOFTWARE_ORCHESTRATION — orchestration / observability / model serving
                          (DDOG, SNOW, MDB, NOW, PLTR, ESTC)
6. AI_NETWORKING        — 800G+ fabric / DPU / smartNIC
                          (AVGO, MRVL, ANET, COHR, LITE, CIEN)
7. MEMORY_HIERARCHY     — CXL / chiplets / 3D stacking dodge HBM tightness
                          (MU, AVGO, MRVL, KLAC, AMAT)
8. LIQUID_COOLING       — thermal density spec lock-in
                          (VRT, NVT, BOYD, ETN, CARR)

Each adaptation:
  - has a CAUSAL RATIONALE explaining the architectural shift
  - is TRIGGERED BY specific SystemNode constraints (HBM tight →
    ALT_ACCELERATOR + MEMORY_HIERARCHY)
  - has a DETECT regex that matches articles using that adaptation's
    language (not company names — concepts: "performance per watt",
    "custom silicon", "behind the meter", "MLOps", "800g fabric")
  - has a SMALL SEED (5-7 canonical tickers) so the graph isn't empty
    on cold start

DYNAMIC LEARNING
  recordBeneficiary() runs on every article that:
    (a) matches an adaptation pattern
    (b) has tickers in ticker_symbols
    (c) passes celebrity-noise + retail-deal filters
  Increments (ticker, adaptation) score by source-tier weight.
  KV-backed at beneficiary:adapt:v1: with 30-day half-life decay.
  New tickers enter the graph organically as they get coverage.

NOISE FIX
  "Dua Lipa sues Samsung" no longer accumulates Samsung under any
  adaptation. CELEBRITY_LEGAL_NOISE filter excludes lawsuits, copyright
  claims, royalty disputes, grammy/oscar references, divorce, etc. from
  both evidence and beneficiary accumulation.

API
  /api/v1/news?persistent=1 now includes architectural_adaptations[]
  per bottleneck — each adaptation lists top-5 beneficiary tickers.

UI
  Persistent Bottleneck cards now show "↪ ARCHITECTURAL BENEFICIARIES
  (2nd-order)" panel with adaptations + tickers + 1-line rationale.

Cache key v27 → v28. tsc clean.

Result: HBM tightness now surfaces ALT_ACCELERATOR (AMD, AVGO) AND
MEMORY_HIERARCHY (MU). Grid constraint surfaces POWER_EFFICIENCY
(ARM, QCOM, AMPC, AAPL) AND BEHIND_THE_METER (BE, BLDP, OKLO).
INTERCONNECT surfaces EDGE_INFERENCE (AKAM, NET, FSLY) — the system
now finds 2nd-order winners that don't appear in supplier lists.
